'''FedACH''' is the [[Federal Reserve Bank]]s' [[Automated Clearing House]] (ACH) service. In 2007, FedACH processed about 37 million transactions per day with an average aggregate value of about $58 billion. For comparison, [[Fedwire]] processed about 537,000 transactions per day valued at nearly $2.7 trillion in the same year.<ref>{{cite book|title=The Department of the Treasury Blueprint for a Modernized Financial Regulatory Structure|page=210|publisher=[[United States Department of the Treasury]]|date=March 2008|url=http://www.treasury.gov/press-center/press-releases/Documents/Blueprint.pdf}}</ref>
